{"000-section": {"000-title": "Pregnant Women Registration in Tamil Nadu for Birth Certificate Under RCH Scheme"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Pregnant Women Registration in Tamil Nadu", "001-normal": "Department of Public Health is the sole body for Registration of Pregnant Women under RCH Scheme. Accordingly, various government hospitals, primary health centers and health sub-centers provides ante-natal care in case of a new born baby. Moreover, Village Health Nurses (VHN) carry out this work in the rural areas while the Urban health Nurses (UHN) carry out this task in urban areas.", "002-normal": "In addition to this, they make registration of the pregnant ladies and also monitor several expectant mothers. For this, these hospitals and nurses observes the details of ante-natal care being given to them. Afterwards, VHNs uploads the documents of the pregnant ladies on the Pregnant and Infant Cohort Monitoring and Evaluation (PICME) software to obtain a 12 digit number \u2013 RCH ID.", "003-normal": "Moreover, candidates can also get this RCH ID at PHCs, Urban PHCs and other govt. hospitals through online registration at PICME. In addition to this, candidates can obtain this RCH ID from Common Service Centers (CSCs) in rural & urban areas or by calling Helpline Number 102.", "004-normal": "Now Pre-registration facility is also available for pregnant women on the official website [picme.tn.gov.in](https://picme.tn.gov.in/) to get their RCH ID."}}